    "title": "Opinion Announcement - June 02, 1997",
    "transcript": {
        "title": null,
        "duration": 143.912,
        "sections": [
            {
                "start": 0,
                "stop": 143.912,
                "byte_start": 28672,
                "byte_stop": 604306,
                "turns": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "stop": 143.912,
                        "byte_start": 28672,
                        "byte_stop": 604306,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.586,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 59079,
                                "text": "I have the opinion of the Court to announce in No. 96-542, McMillian versus Monroe County."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 7.586,
                                "stop": 21.191,
                                "byte_start": 59079,
                                "byte_stop": 113518,
                                "text": "In this case, Walter McMillian sued Tom Tate, the Sheriff of Monroe County, Alabama, and the County itself claiming that they had violated his constitutional right to due process of law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 21.191,
                                "stop": 31.66,
                                "byte_start": 113518,
                                "byte_stop": 155314,
                                "text": "Under our precedents, Monroe County can be held liable under Section 1983 only if Sheriff Tate is the so-called county policymaker."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 31.66,
                                "stop": 45.005,
                                "byte_start": 155314,
                                "byte_stop": 208708,
                                "text": "It is clear that Sheriff Tate is a law enforcement policymaker, but the question which must be asked here is whether the Sheriff represents the County or the State of Alabama when he acts in that capacity."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.005,
                                "stop": 53.922,
                                "byte_start": 208708,
                                "byte_stop": 244443,
                                "text": "The District Court decided the Sheriff was a state policymaker, not a county policymaker, but the Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 53.922,
                                "stop": 59.454,
                                "byte_start": 244443,
                                "byte_stop": 266491,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the Clerk today, we affirm the judgment of the Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.454,
                                "stop": 69.637,
                                "byte_start": 266491,
                                "byte_stop": 307242,
                                "text": "Because our analysis is dependent on state law, we defer considerably to the Court of Appeals\u0027 expertise in interpreting the law of the States in which it sits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 69.637,
                                "stop": 76.109,
                                "byte_start": 307242,
                                "byte_stop": 333155,
                                "text": "And the Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit sits in Alabama, Georgia, and Florida."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.109,
                                "stop": 88.314,
                                "byte_start": 333155,
                                "byte_stop": 381952,
                                "text": "All six Alabama Constitutions from the 1819 version to the current one have made sure of State Executive Branch officials alongside the Governor and the Attorney General."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.314,
                                "stop": 102.691,
                                "byte_start": 381952,
                                "byte_stop": 439526,
                                "text": "The Alabama Supreme Court, in deciding whether the State or the County is liable on when sheriffs commit torts has interpreted the Alabama Constitution to mean that the sheriff is a state official not a county official."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.691,
                                "stop": 110.023,
                                "byte_start": 439526,
                                "byte_stop": 468783,
                                "text": "The petitioner points to decisions in which sheriffs of other States have been held to be county policymakers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 110.023,
                                "stop": 112.852,
                                "byte_start": 468783,
                                "byte_stop": 480172,
                                "text": "And we, in no sense, dispute those holdings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.852,
                                "stop": 122.877,
                                "byte_start": 480172,
                                "byte_stop": 520192,
                                "text": "One of the principal virtues of our Federal system is that the States are given wide authority to set up State and Local Governments as they wish."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.877,
                                "stop": 127.639,
                                "byte_start": 520192,
                                "byte_stop": 539314,
                                "text": "And what may be true of a particular officer in one State may not be in another."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 127.639,
                                "stop": 136.558,
                                "byte_start": 539314,
                                "byte_stop": 574945,
                                "text": "Thus, it is entirely possible for sheriffs in Alabama to be state officials and for sheriffs in other States to be county officials."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 136.558,
                                "stop": 143.912,
                                "byte_start": 574945,
                                "byte_stop": 604306,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justices Stevens, Souter, and Breyer joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
